WEBVTT

00:00:01.704 --> 00:00:03.975
AKIRA: Kencho, Shizuka,

00:00:04.008 --> 00:00:06.379
have either of you heard
of mindfulness?

00:00:06.413 --> 00:00:08.685
- Immersing yourself in
the present

00:00:08.718 --> 00:00:11.891
and freeing yourself from both
the past and future, right?

00:00:11.924 --> 00:00:14.128
We covered that
in corporate seminars.

00:00:14.162 --> 00:00:17.234
- That's right,
and moving forward,

00:00:17.268 --> 00:00:20.609
I'm aspiring to maintain
that mindset whenever I can.

00:00:20.642 --> 00:00:25.250
- Okay, listen, Akira.
No offense, but...

00:00:25.283 --> 00:00:28.022
I don't think you need
to worry about maintaining

00:00:28.056 --> 00:00:30.661
your mindfulness
or whatever it is you call it.

00:00:32.865 --> 00:00:34.168
[motorcycle
engine revving]

00:00:34.202 --> 00:00:36.005
<i>AKIRA: Oh, man,
things are going great!</i>

00:00:36.038 --> 00:00:38.911
I've already crossed
15 things off my list!

00:00:38.945 --> 00:00:42.318
At this rate I might be
able to finish it within one
month!

00:00:42.351 --> 00:00:46.092
- I feel like you might
get eaten by a zombie if you do.

00:00:46.125 --> 00:00:47.830
- How much longer
till we're there?

00:00:47.863 --> 00:00:49.600
- I'd say about an hour!

00:00:49.633 --> 00:00:51.870
- That's only
if nothing else happens.

00:00:51.904 --> 00:00:55.277
Just look how long it took
for us to get here from Tokyo.

00:00:55.310 --> 00:00:56.747
<i>- I'm sure we'll
get there before</i>

00:00:56.781 --> 00:00:57.716
<i>the end of summer!</i>

00:00:57.749 --> 00:00:59.084
[both laughing]

00:00:59.118 --> 00:01:00.220
all: Huh?

00:01:00.253 --> 00:01:03.192
[tires squealing]

00:01:04.897 --> 00:01:06.767
KENCHO: What's going on?

00:01:06.800 --> 00:01:07.970
AKIRA: A survivor?

00:01:08.003 --> 00:01:10.441
SHIZUKA: They lost a wheel
and can't move!

00:01:10.474 --> 00:01:11.643
- All right!

00:01:11.677 --> 00:01:14.448
It's been a while,
but it's shark suit time!

00:01:14.482 --> 00:01:17.320
- What the--
you're charging in there?

00:01:17.354 --> 00:01:19.291
Guess I shouldn't be
that surprised.

00:01:20.361 --> 00:01:22.364
AKIRA: Stop right there,
zombies!

00:01:22.397 --> 00:01:25.871
Your diabolical reign
of terror ends here!

00:01:25.905 --> 00:01:27.642
[grunting]

00:01:27.675 --> 00:01:31.049
'Cause Akiranger is here!
Super hero of justi--

00:01:31.082 --> 00:01:32.017
[zombies groaning]

00:01:32.051 --> 00:01:33.419
Huh?

00:01:36.058 --> 00:01:37.394
[zombie groans]

00:01:40.233 --> 00:01:41.503
[all gasping]

00:01:43.574 --> 00:01:44.509
[zombies groaning]

00:01:45.578 --> 00:01:46.713
- [gasping]

00:01:49.619 --> 00:01:50.655
[zombies groaning]

00:01:50.688 --> 00:01:51.823
- [stammering]

00:01:57.635 --> 00:02:00.173
[zombies groaning]

00:02:07.789 --> 00:02:10.193
[BEATRIX exhales]

00:02:10.227 --> 00:02:12.231
- Is this a period drama?

00:02:12.264 --> 00:02:14.335
AKIRA: That was so cool!

00:02:14.369 --> 00:02:16.372
- [speaking German]

00:02:16.405 --> 00:02:18.711
I owe you all a debt
of gratitude

00:02:18.744 --> 00:02:20.080
for assisting me here.

00:02:20.113 --> 00:02:21.717
AKIRA: Huh?

00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:25.559
- Thank you.
My name is Beatrix Amerhauser.

00:02:25.592 --> 00:02:27.361
[grunts]

00:02:27.395 --> 00:02:29.131
- Hold up.
A foreigner?

00:02:29.164 --> 00:02:31.102
- Uh, a girl?

00:02:31.135 --> 00:02:33.206
- Where do I start?
Goodness.

00:02:34.375 --> 00:02:36.379
[Kana-Boon's "Song of the Dead"]

00:04:06.827 --> 00:04:09.432
- So then you came here
from Germany because you're

00:04:09.465 --> 00:04:11.570
a fan of Japan, Beatrix?

00:04:11.604 --> 00:04:12.639
- Oh, ja!

00:04:12.672 --> 00:04:15.344
Nippon's culture
is truly magnificent!

00:04:15.377 --> 00:04:18.617
Kyoto, Fuji-yama,
and ikebana.

00:04:18.651 --> 00:04:22.592
I love each part of this country
and studied them greatly!

00:04:22.625 --> 00:04:24.729
- Well, that explains the armor.

00:04:24.762 --> 00:04:26.199
- I have to say,

00:04:26.232 --> 00:04:28.704
it's not a bad
anti-zombie strategy.

00:04:28.737 --> 00:04:29.973
[doors creak]

00:04:30.006 --> 00:04:32.177
- Refrigeration.

00:04:32.210 --> 00:04:34.182
AKIRA: For fish?

00:04:34.215 --> 00:04:35.618
- It may seem strange,

00:04:35.651 --> 00:04:39.024
but I have reasons
to see this fish delivered.

00:04:39.058 --> 00:04:42.131
However, I can't anymore.

00:04:42.164 --> 00:04:44.536
Seems that you
are all brave samurai.

00:04:44.569 --> 00:04:46.707
May I request your aid?

00:04:46.741 --> 00:04:49.478
Though it may not be
your destination,

00:04:49.513 --> 00:04:52.552
would you mind helping me
deliver this fish to Takasaki?

00:04:52.585 --> 00:04:53.788
- Huh?

00:04:53.821 --> 00:04:56.860
- I suppose we could stop by
Takasaki City.

00:04:56.894 --> 00:04:59.699
- If she's transporting all
these fish to survivors

00:04:59.733 --> 00:05:01.402
then we should help,
don't you think?

00:05:01.435 --> 00:05:04.008
- But there are risks involved
with going near a city.

00:05:04.041 --> 00:05:05.310
- Huh?

00:05:05.343 --> 00:05:07.949
- Why are you transporting fish?

00:05:07.982 --> 00:05:10.454
- Ever since I was exposed
to Nippon's culture

00:05:10.487 --> 00:05:12.024
on TV as a child,

00:05:12.057 --> 00:05:13.727
I've dreamed of coming here

00:05:13.761 --> 00:05:16.165
and seeing it
for myself someday.

00:05:16.199 --> 00:05:18.671
After saving money
from multiple jobs,

00:05:18.705 --> 00:05:21.208
the day came where I landed
in Narita,

00:05:21.242 --> 00:05:23.246
but the pandemic already--

00:05:23.279 --> 00:05:26.520
and so the beautiful Nippon
I've once dreamed of visiting

00:05:26.553 --> 00:05:29.091
was gone forever.

00:05:29.124 --> 00:05:32.765
But after admiring
Nippon's culture for so long,

00:05:32.799 --> 00:05:35.972
I just had to see it
and experience it for myself,

00:05:36.005 --> 00:05:38.409
and at last,
I found it.

00:05:38.442 --> 00:05:42.350
The only one remaining--
the last sushi chef alive!

00:05:42.384 --> 00:05:44.856
- What?
- Sushi?

00:05:44.890 --> 00:05:47.328
- The taisho
of this sushiya told me

00:05:47.361 --> 00:05:48.697
if I could deliver fish,

00:05:48.731 --> 00:05:50.568
he would let me eat
as much as I want

00:05:50.601 --> 00:05:52.572
of his delicious sushi!

00:05:52.605 --> 00:05:55.778
<i>both: So she's just in it
for sushi?</i>

00:05:56.312 --> 00:05:58.617
- Beatrix.

00:05:58.651 --> 00:06:01.322
AKIRA: It's clear to me
that your love of Japan

00:06:01.355 --> 00:06:03.928
and its culture
is pure and true.

00:06:03.961 --> 00:06:05.564
Don't you worry!

00:06:05.598 --> 00:06:07.869
We will deliver that fish,

00:06:07.902 --> 00:06:10.340
even if it costs all
of us our very lives!

00:06:10.373 --> 00:06:13.146
<i>both: He's only in it
for the sushi, too!</i>

00:06:13.180 --> 00:06:14.849
- [speaking German]

00:06:14.882 --> 00:06:17.689
I knew when I saw you,
you were all true samurai!

00:06:17.722 --> 00:06:20.795
AKIRA: Now that that's decide,
let's hurry, you two!

00:06:20.828 --> 00:06:22.031
Come on, guys!

00:06:22.064 --> 00:06:25.103
The fish is losing its quality
each minute that passes!

00:06:25.136 --> 00:06:28.276
AKIRA: It's time we show her
the spirit of hospitality!

00:06:28.309 --> 00:06:30.582
[both grunting]

00:06:30.615 --> 00:06:33.153
<i>BEATRIX: The sushiya
is located down an alleyway</i>

00:06:33.186 --> 00:06:35.190
<i>just past central Ginza.</i>

00:06:35.224 --> 00:06:36.593
<i>AKIRA: Back alley?</i>

00:06:36.627 --> 00:06:38.430
<i>Sounds like it's full
of character!</i>

00:06:38.463 --> 00:06:40.835
It's gotta be famous, right?

00:06:40.868 --> 00:06:44.074
- However, the last time
I talked to him over the phone

00:06:44.108 --> 00:06:45.745
was three days ago.

00:06:45.778 --> 00:06:48.550
I sure hope the taisho
is all right.

00:06:49.986 --> 00:06:51.088
- Huh?

00:06:51.122 --> 00:06:54.261
KENCHO: Whoa, this place
is packed with zombies.

00:06:54.294 --> 00:06:56.733
AKIRA: Well, Beatrix,
are you ready?

00:06:56.767 --> 00:06:58.804
BEATRIX: Hai.
On your mark.

00:06:58.838 --> 00:07:01.577
- Look, uh, it's nice you two
are motivated,

00:07:01.610 --> 00:07:04.014
but you guys have a plan at all?

00:07:04.048 --> 00:07:05.116
- Nope!
- Nein!

00:07:05.150 --> 00:07:06.252
- [exhales sharply]

00:07:06.285 --> 00:07:07.956
Chargin' in head-first
as always.

00:07:07.989 --> 00:07:09.058
Am I right?

00:07:09.091 --> 00:07:11.062
- I might have a plan
to deal with this.

00:07:11.095 --> 00:07:12.999
- What?

00:07:13.032 --> 00:07:14.401
SHIZUKA: Hmm.

00:07:14.435 --> 00:07:17.407
"All under heaven is not
for one man,

00:07:17.441 --> 00:07:20.146
but for all men,"
so if we're gonna do this,

00:07:20.179 --> 00:07:21.750
we're gonna pig out on sushi.

00:07:21.783 --> 00:07:24.622
- So, we're Three Kingdoms now?

00:07:24.656 --> 00:07:28.463
KENCHO: Hey, zombies!
This way, you dummies!

00:07:28.496 --> 00:07:31.402
You want a tasty piece of ass,
don't ya?

00:07:31.435 --> 00:07:33.472
Then come get it!

00:07:34.575 --> 00:07:36.345
[all groaning]

00:07:36.379 --> 00:07:38.182
[breathing heavily]

00:07:38.216 --> 00:07:40.220
This way!

00:07:40.253 --> 00:07:42.525
Come on!
Now, Akira!

00:07:42.558 --> 00:07:43.694
[tires squealing]

00:07:43.728 --> 00:07:45.898
[truck horn honking]

00:07:45.932 --> 00:07:47.669
- Beatrix!

00:07:47.702 --> 00:07:49.438
- Right!
Leave this to me!

00:07:49.472 --> 00:07:53.179
[shouting]

00:07:53.212 --> 00:07:56.118
[zombies groaning]

00:07:58.223 --> 00:08:01.128
[horn honking continues]

00:08:02.097 --> 00:08:04.736
[zombies groaning]

00:08:05.704 --> 00:08:07.775
AKIRA: Shizuka!
[grunts]

00:08:07.808 --> 00:08:09.646
I gathered as many as I could.

00:08:09.679 --> 00:08:11.449
- Whew, so, everything work out?

00:08:11.482 --> 00:08:12.519
- Yes.

00:08:12.552 --> 00:08:14.623
Exactly as I planned it.

00:08:14.656 --> 00:08:15.958
KENCHO: All right!

00:08:16.459 --> 00:08:17.695
[grunts]

00:08:17.728 --> 00:08:21.268
[glass shattering]
[zombies groaning]

00:08:21.301 --> 00:08:23.339
[both grunting]

00:08:23.373 --> 00:08:26.245
[distant glass shattering]

00:08:27.682 --> 00:08:30.053
- And so the time has come.

00:08:31.455 --> 00:08:34.095
Now, then,
unleash the flames upon them!

00:08:34.128 --> 00:08:35.163
both: Right!

00:08:35.196 --> 00:08:36.866
- Time for a barbecue!

00:08:37.902 --> 00:08:38.637
all: Huh?

00:08:38.670 --> 00:08:42.310
[zombies groaning]

00:08:42.343 --> 00:08:44.448
- Hey, were there always
this many?

00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:45.585
Huh?

00:08:45.618 --> 00:08:46.753
SHIZUKA: Hurry and light it!

00:08:46.786 --> 00:08:49.024
BEATRIX: J--Ja!
AKIRA: Okay!

00:08:49.058 --> 00:08:51.295
Ah, well, it's, uh--
- It's no use!

00:08:51.328 --> 00:08:53.032
This match doesn't want
to light!

00:08:53.065 --> 00:08:54.101
SHIZUKA: Hurry up!

00:08:56.406 --> 00:08:59.311
- [grunts]
This is bad!

00:08:59.344 --> 00:09:03.185
KENCHO: At this rate our RV's
gonna be buried in zombies!

00:09:04.054 --> 00:09:05.023
- You're kidding.

00:09:05.056 --> 00:09:08.296
But if that happens,
the fish will be...

00:09:08.329 --> 00:09:11.637
BEATRIX: We can't fight
that many of them head-on.

00:09:11.670 --> 00:09:13.741
It's all over for us!

00:09:13.774 --> 00:09:15.577
AKIRA: Fear...
- Huh?

00:09:15.611 --> 00:09:18.917
AKIRA: Is nothing more than
an excuse not to act.

00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:21.189
It's not about whether we can.

00:09:21.222 --> 00:09:24.295
It's about whether we have
the desire to do it!

00:09:24.328 --> 00:09:26.198
The want to do it!

00:09:26.232 --> 00:09:27.602
- [gasps]

00:09:27.636 --> 00:09:31.142
<i>both: He just wants
to each sushi.</i>

00:09:31.175 --> 00:09:33.814
AKIRA: If we can't sit and eat
at a nice sushi restaurant,

00:09:33.847 --> 00:09:36.318
then I'd rather become a zombie!

00:09:36.352 --> 00:09:37.721
- [gasps]

00:09:39.058 --> 00:09:40.226
Oh?

00:09:47.407 --> 00:09:48.877
[gasps]

00:09:50.013 --> 00:09:52.083
- Incoming!

00:09:53.219 --> 00:09:55.657
[grunting]
[zombie groans]

00:09:56.425 --> 00:09:57.762
[grunting]

00:09:57.796 --> 00:09:59.364
[breathing heavily]

00:10:01.035 --> 00:10:01.837
Huh?

00:10:01.870 --> 00:10:03.740
- [speaking Japanese]

00:10:04.642 --> 00:10:06.378
[zombies groaning]

00:10:06.412 --> 00:10:08.283
- Beatrix!

00:10:08.316 --> 00:10:10.420
BEATRIX: I apologize
for the shameful behavior

00:10:10.453 --> 00:10:12.525
I exhibited.

00:10:12.558 --> 00:10:14.361
I will no longer waiver.

00:10:15.531 --> 00:10:17.535
- [grunts]

00:10:17.569 --> 00:10:20.006
BEATRIX: Let's do this, Akira!
AKIRA: Right!

00:10:20.039 --> 00:10:21.175
[both grunting]

00:10:30.026 --> 00:10:32.464
[both shouting]

00:10:32.497 --> 00:10:35.638
[zombies groaning]

00:10:35.671 --> 00:10:38.375
- [shouting]

00:10:40.079 --> 00:10:41.415
[zombies shouting]

00:10:42.451 --> 00:10:44.087
[grunting]

00:10:50.266 --> 00:10:52.337
Huh?
Uh, Akira!

00:10:52.370 --> 00:10:54.040
- Leave it to me!

00:10:54.074 --> 00:10:55.276
[grunting]

00:10:58.951 --> 00:11:00.086
[grunts]

00:11:00.119 --> 00:11:01.856
[zombie groaning]

00:11:03.125 --> 00:11:05.197
You!
Oh, man!

00:11:05.230 --> 00:11:06.198
They just keep coming!

00:11:06.231 --> 00:11:08.102
BEATRIX: At this rate,
we will be...

00:11:08.135 --> 00:11:09.839
[distant music playing]
both: Huh?

00:11:09.872 --> 00:11:13.246
<i>["Sakura" playing
over drone]</i>

00:11:13.279 --> 00:11:15.685
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:11:15.718 --> 00:11:18.422
Wait.
That's my Walkman!

00:11:19.893 --> 00:11:22.230
SHIZUKA: And just to be
safe... - [grunts]

00:11:24.301 --> 00:11:27.006
BEATRIX: Here,
and if you don't mind my asking,

00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:29.077
what do you need
my Walkman for?

00:11:29.110 --> 00:11:31.181
- We don't know what
will happen out there

00:11:31.215 --> 00:11:33.754
so we should prepare
a backup plan.

00:11:33.787 --> 00:11:35.456
- This is...

00:11:35.489 --> 00:11:37.862
[both gasping]

00:11:37.895 --> 00:11:40.166
The zombies are...

00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:42.037
AKIRA: They're getting
lured away!

00:11:42.070 --> 00:11:45.911
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:11:45.945 --> 00:11:49.586
- I didn't wanna do this because
it would cause more damage

00:11:49.619 --> 00:11:51.723
but I have no choice.

00:11:51.757 --> 00:11:54.194
Once again the
time has come.

00:11:54.930 --> 00:11:56.365
Unleash the flames!

00:11:56.398 --> 00:11:58.937
- [shouting]

00:12:01.241 --> 00:12:02.310
[glass shattering]

00:12:02.343 --> 00:12:03.913
[zombies shouting]

00:12:05.116 --> 00:12:07.353
[booming]

00:12:08.924 --> 00:12:11.963
[zombies roaring]

00:12:16.506 --> 00:12:19.444
[all shouting]

00:12:26.358 --> 00:12:27.695
[all laughing]

00:12:27.728 --> 00:12:29.497
- Oh, yeah!

00:12:29.532 --> 00:12:34.976
Tonight we're pigging out
on fancy all-you-can-eat sushi!

00:12:37.582 --> 00:12:39.619
<i>all: So good!</i>

00:12:39.652 --> 00:12:40.988
What the hell?

00:12:41.021 --> 00:12:43.927
It's so good,
it just melts in my mouth!

00:12:43.961 --> 00:12:46.264
- The vinegar
and rice falls apart perfectly

00:12:46.298 --> 00:12:48.703
and it's prepared with such care
I couldn't find a critique

00:12:48.737 --> 00:12:50.674
for this if I tried!

00:12:50.708 --> 00:12:52.845
- It's firm with
the right amount of sweetness!

00:12:52.878 --> 00:12:54.849
The fancy food I
had entertaining clients

00:12:54.882 --> 00:12:56.352
wasn't this good!

00:12:56.385 --> 00:12:59.391
- It may be true I moved
back home to Gunma,

00:12:59.424 --> 00:13:01.730
but before that I'd been honing
my skills

00:13:01.763 --> 00:13:03.867
for nearly 30 years in Tsukiji.

00:13:03.900 --> 00:13:05.804
Despite it being the end
of the world,

00:13:05.838 --> 00:13:07.407
you came to eat my sushi!

00:13:07.440 --> 00:13:10.179
For that,
you can eat as much as you like!

00:13:10.212 --> 00:13:12.718
- I think I'd like to try
the gizzard shot next!

00:13:12.751 --> 00:13:13.820
- More cold sake!

00:13:13.853 --> 00:13:15.323
AKIRA: Oh, yum!

00:13:15.356 --> 00:13:17.561
It's so tasty,
I could eat this forever!

00:13:17.594 --> 00:13:18.964
- [whimpering]
KENCHO: Ooh!

00:13:18.997 --> 00:13:21.368
Fancy sushi restaurants
are the best!

00:13:24.542 --> 00:13:26.011
- [gasps]

00:13:27.347 --> 00:13:28.817
- [exhales]

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:30.955
Beatrix, what do you think?

00:13:30.988 --> 00:13:32.491
[Beatrix sniffles]

00:13:32.525 --> 00:13:34.962
It's--it's bitter.

00:13:34.996 --> 00:13:38.670
It's bittersweet
but still delicious.

00:13:38.703 --> 00:13:41.877
I really am so happy to be here.

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:43.714
- [laughing]

00:13:43.747 --> 00:13:45.450
all: Welcome to Japan.

00:13:45.483 --> 00:13:48.657
TAISHO: I can't believe
you're shedding tears over my
sushi!

00:13:48.690 --> 00:13:50.026
[crying]

00:13:50.060 --> 00:13:52.598
I worked every day without
any days off even

00:13:52.631 --> 00:13:55.905
