are continuously shunned

00:21:00.052 --> 00:21:01.421
and ignored,

00:21:01.454 --> 00:21:04.327
it makes it hard to accept
the opinions of others.

00:21:04.360 --> 00:21:06.464
In order to defend
your position,

00:21:06.498 --> 00:21:09.705
you assert your legitimacy
by rejecting

00:21:09.738 --> 00:21:12.109
what other people
have to say.

00:21:12.143 --> 00:21:14.849
SHIZUKA: But you're
not concerned

00:21:14.882 --> 00:21:16.284
about winning approval.

00:21:16.317 --> 00:21:18.789
You just say whatever comes
to your mind.

00:21:20.126 --> 00:21:23.332
I guess that made me
a little jealous.

00:21:23.365 --> 00:21:25.603
And the old me slipped out
for a bit.

00:21:27.908 --> 00:21:29.244
SHIZUKA: The truth is,

00:21:29.277 --> 00:21:31.381
I'm just bad at romance.

00:21:32.518 --> 00:21:35.089
I'm afraid of getting hurt.

00:21:35.122 --> 00:21:38.295
Which is probably why I put up
a front and acted like work

00:21:38.329 --> 00:21:40.366
was more important.

00:21:40.399 --> 00:21:42.771
AKIRA: Wow, Shizuka.
You're, uh--

00:21:42.805 --> 00:21:43.906
- [gasps]

00:21:45.577 --> 00:21:48.348
- You're being really open
right now.

00:21:48.382 --> 00:21:49.651
- [grunts]

00:21:51.054 --> 00:21:55.430
If one day I do find
myself falling in love...

00:21:55.463 --> 00:21:57.968
I can only hope that it's
with someone I

00:21:58.001 --> 00:21:59.638
can be this open with.

